                <note rend="inline" type="source">863.51 Relief Credits/116: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Herrick</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-05-29T17:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 29, 1928—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 29—3:32 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>139. Reparation 95. Reference paragraph one, my Reparation 93, May 27. I
                    understand Italian representative on Relief Bonds Committee now opposes the
                    Austrian loan on much the same grounds as those advanced by the Italian
                    delegation at the Reparation Commission meeting on May 27.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Herrick</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
